2014|date=January 25, 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150109003027/http://www.pep.ph/news/16199/TV-Ratings-%28Jan.-22-24%29:-Coffee-Prince-and-Lastikman-moving-up|archive-date=January 9, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> The series was re-aired with English subtitles on [[Animax Asia]] in 2010, and on [[GMA News TV]] from September 19 to October 14, 2016 at 11:00pm.\n\nIt aired in Thailand on [[Channel 7 (Thailand)|Channel 7]] beginning April 19, 2008.<ref>{{cite web|title=TV Ratings (Jan. 22-24): ''Coffee Prince'' and ''Lastikman'' moving up|url=http://guru.sanook.com/5531/|work=Sanook.com|accessdate=November 26, 2013|date=August 18, 2015}} {{lang-th|\u0e20\u0e32\u0e29\u0e32\u0e44\u0e17\u0e22}}</ref>\n\nThe series aired in Malaysia in 2010 on [[Animax Asia]] with Malay Dub and English subtitles.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.facebook.com/animaxasiatv/posts/119253794761750 |title = Animax Asia}}</ref>\n\nIt aired in the Middle East on [[MBC 4 (Middle East)|MBC 4]] beginning December 8, 2013, [[dubbing (filmmaking)|dubbed]] as ''Makha al amir''.\n\nIt was dubbed in [[Tamil language|Tamil]] and aired in [[India]] on [[Puthuyugam TV]] beginning October 2014.\n\nIt is currently aired in [[Chile]] on [[ETC (Chilean TV channel)]] beginning September 2016.\n\n==Remake==\n{{main|Coffee Prince (2012 TV series)}}\nIn 2012, the TV series was [[remake|remade]] in [[Thailand]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Brewing up a rich drama|url=http://www.bangkokpost.com/arts-and-culture/tv-and-radio/299175/brewing-up-a-rich-drama|work=[[Bangkok Post]]|accessdate=March 7, 2013|date=June 22, 2012}}</ref> and the [[Philippines]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Kris Bernal and Aljur Abrenica's ''Coffee Prince'' becomes trending topic on Twitter|url=http://pep.ph/guide/tv/10922/kris-bernal-and-aljur-abrenica39s-coffee-prince-becomes-trending-topic-on-twitter|work=[[Philippine Entertainment Portal]]|accessdate=March 7, 2013|date=October 9, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, a Chinese remake of the series titled ''Prince Coffee Lab'' was announced, directed by Kang Shin-hyo of ''[[The Heirs]]''.<ref>https://www.dramafever.com/news/coffee-prince-set-for-chinese-remake-with-the-director-of-heirs/</ref>\n\nIn 2017, the Malaysian remake of ''Coffee Prince'' directed by Michael Ang began airing on [[Astro Ria]] starting November 28.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.astrogempak.com.my/artikel/5687/fattah-amin-hero-coffee-prince-malaysia-a-big-no-ini-reaksi-peminat-drama-korea/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=July 20, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170715124859/http://www.astrogempak.com.my/artikel/5687/fattah-amin-hero-coffee-prince-malaysia-a-big-no-ini-reaksi-peminat-drama-korea |archive-date=July 15, 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|The 1st Shop of Coffee Prince}}\n* {{Official website|http://imbc.com/broad/tv/drama/coffeeprince/}} {{in lang|ko}}\n* {{hancinema drama|Coffee_Prince}}\n* {{IMDb title|1772685}}\n\n[[Category:Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation television dramas]]\n[[Category:2007 South Korean television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2007 South Korean television series endings]]\n[[Category:2000s South Korean television series]]\n[[Category:Korean-language television programs]]\n[[Category:South Korean romantic comedy television series]]\n[[Category:Television series set in restaurants]]\n[[Category:Works about coffee]]\n[[Category:Television programs based on South Korean novels]]\n", "name_user": "Bagoto", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coffee_Prince_(2007_TV_series)"}
